daily_summary.headline: Artemis II and Starlink Launches Dominate the Day

top_events.title: Artemis II Crewed Mission
top_events.description: The Artemis II mission is set to send a crew of 4 astronauts on a lunar flyby, marking a significant milestone in NASA's Artemis program.
top_events.action: Watch the live stream and follow the mission updates.

top_events.title: Starlink Group 17-32 Deployment
top_events.description: SpaceX's Falcon 9 will deploy a batch of 25 Starlink satellites, expanding the global internet constellation.
top_events.action: Tune in to the live webcast for the launch.

top_events.title: Soyuz 2.1a/Fregat-M Launch
top_events.description: A Soyuz 2.1a rocket will launch a classified payload for the Russian military from Plesetsk Cosmodrome.
top_events.action: Follow updates from Russian Space Forces.
